File: Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane outlined the amended lockdown regulations for the tourism sector. JOHANNESBURG - Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane outlined the amended lockdown regulations for the tourism sector. The minister used the briefing to detail interventions to mitigate the impact of the pandemic on the sector. READ: Tourism sector urged to use winter season to gear up The industry has been hard hit with holiday and leisure facilities being shut down during the lockdown. This has resulted in millions of rands being lost in revenue. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.